alisbury/"}]},"prices":{"avgSold12Mo":null,"source":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/SP2.html","asOf":"2026-05-24"},"thingsToDo":["Village and valley walks","Visits to Salisbury Cathedral/cultural venues","Trips to local heritage sites and surrounding countryside"],"placesToEat":["Country pubs in surrounding villages","Wider restaurant and café options in Salisbury"],"pros":["Quieter environment than central Salisbury","Reasonable access to city services and rail via Salisbury station"],"cons":["Many errands still require driving","Public transport coverage varies by village and time of day"],"whoItSuits":"Best for buyers prioritising village character and countryside access, while accepting regular trips into Salisbury for wider amenities and commuting connections.","broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bemerton","https://www.wiltshire.gov.uk/","https://get-information-schools.service.gov.uk/","https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/SP2.html","https://www.nationalrail.co.uk/stations/salisbury/","https://www.google.com/maps"]},{"id":"bentworth-gu34","name":"Bentworth","village":"Bentworth","town":"Winchester","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"GU34","hubCity":"Guildford","regionDir":"","settlementType":"","subRegion":"Winchester","coords":{"lat":51.15176,"lng":-0.96956},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"researched","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"Bentworth is a substantial village and civil parish in East Hampshire, west of Alton in the GU34 area. It has medieval roots, a notable church heritage and a long-established agricultural setting on higher ground. Modern Bentworth combines historic lanes and period property with active parish life and access to Alton’s rail and shopping services.","character":"Historic hill village with period homes, parish facilities and a strong rural landscape setting.","amenities":[