ants on/near the high street","Additional dining choices in Wickham and Fareham corridor"],"pros":["Strong amenity base compared with many nearby villages","Historic character with active community life"],"cons":["Traffic/parking pressure at peak times in town centre","Rail access requires travel to nearby stations"],"whoItSuits":"Very suitable for families and professionals seeking a characterful small-town base with useful daily amenities, good school options and reasonable road links to larger employment centres.","broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[{"label":"Wikipedia — Bishop’s Waltham","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bishop%27s_Waltham"},{"label":"English Heritage — Bishop’s Waltham Palace","url":"https://www.english-heritage.org.uk/visit/places/bishops-waltham-palace/"},{"label":"Rightmove House Prices SO32","url":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/SO32.html"},{"label":"Bishop’s Waltham Infant School","url":"https://www.bwschool.org.uk/"}]},{"id":"bishopdown-sp1","name":"Bishopdown","village":"Bishopdown","town":"Salisbury","county":"Wiltshire","postcode":"SP1","hubCity":"Salisbury","regionDir":"","settlementType":"","subRegion":"Salisbury","coords":{"lat":51.07108,"lng":-1.77688},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"researched","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"Bishopdown is in the Salisbury area of Wiltshire (SP1), and sits in the rural-to-commuter belt around Salisbury. Historic references and parish records show long-established settlement patterns, with modern housing mostly as infill around older cores. Day-to-day life depends on local village facilities plus Salisbury for larger services. The area appeals to buyers who want a quieter setting but still need practical links to the city.","character":"Bishopdown has a village-scale layout with mixed period and modern homes, a parish-centred feel, and surrounding countryside as a do